translated: Kuylenstierna, Adolf Fredrik, practicing physician, Gothenburg, b. 23/10/69 in Stig-tomta, Södermanland, 1st son of Johan Frans Gustaf K. and Agnes Bäckgren. Married in 1901 to Anna Selma Kristina Gestrin. Children: Karin Ida Agnes Madeleine. — Completed the medical exam in 1888 and obtained a degree in medical philosophy in 1890 from Uppsala University. Completed a medical degree in 1895 and a medical licentiate in 1900 in Stockholm. Engaged in study trips abroad from 1901-1909 and 1921-1931. Worked as an assistant physician at Sätra brunn from 1893-1896, at Garnisonssjukhuset in Stockholm in 1897, as a medical fellow for the navy from 1898-1901, as a physician at Tranås vattenkur-anstalt from 1901-1905, as an interim district physician in Tranås for a short period from 1901-1904, as a naval physician of the second degree in reserve in 1903, at the Military Medical Corps from 1903-1915, as a naval physician of the first degree in reserve from 1916-1917, and in reserve from 1917-1921, as the principal naval physician in reserve from 1920-1924, as well as various naval command positions. Served on the Drott during three summers and as the head physician at the navy's Gothenburg division from 1914-1916. Worked as a physician and head of the Gothenburg city polyclinic for ear, nose, and throat diseases from 1915-1934, as well as interim department physician at Sahlgr. hospital's ear clinic from 1916-1919. Former chairman of the Gothenburg Medical Society, honorary member since 1940. Recipient of the Royal Order of Vasa, Knight of the Order of the Polar Star 3rd class.
